TY  - JOUR
AU  - Gale, Douglas
T1  - Standard Securities
PY  - 1992
Y1  - 1992/09/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297995
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 59
IS  - 4
SP  - 731
EP  - 755
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - The cost of gathering information about unfamiliar securities may lead to gains from standardization: firms issue a particular security because it is used by other firms. To support standardization as an equilibrium phenomenon, information must be non-transferable (otherwise it might be revealed by prices or the observation of other agents' decisions) and it must be generic (useful in evaluating a number of securities). A competitive equilibrium in which standard contracts are used may be subject to coordination failure: while there always exists a constrained efficient equilibrium, there may also exist Pareto-ranked equilibria.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297995
ER  - 



